<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="349" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1787,2030]" pageId="2" pageNumber="349">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,1787,1812]" pageId="2" pageNumber="349">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Antenna brown, except for pedicel yellow. Scutum pale brown, except for broad median stripe, notopleuron, narrow region above notopleuron, scutellum and mediotergite dark brown (
<figureCitation box="[1179,1251,1822,1847]" captionStart="FIGURES 5–8" captionStartId="3.[151,264,987,1009]" captionTargetBox="[188,1398,193,965]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[188,1398,193,965]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 5–8. Chvalaea Papp &amp; Földvári. 5–6. Mediotergite. 5. Chvalaea pulchra Ale-Rocha, 2006, large central black mark highlighted; 6: Chvalaea annularis sp. nov. 7–8. Hind femur. 7. Chvalaea pulchra Ale-Rocha, 2006; 8. Chvalaea annularis sp. nov., black medium ring highlighted. Scale bars: Figs 5–6 = 0.2 mm; Figs 7–8 = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2612709/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="349">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
). Pleura brown, except upper margin of anepisternum and laterotergite yellow. Wing with veins M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1112,1120,1874,1888]" fontSize="6" pageId="2" pageNumber="349">1</subScript>
and M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1207,1215,1874,1888]" fontSize="6" pageId="2" pageNumber="349">4</subScript>
not reaching wing margin (
<figureCitation box="[244,328,1897,1922]" captionStart="FIGURES 45–52" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1529,1551]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,450,1499]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[151,1436,447,1507]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 45–52. Chvalaea Papp &amp; Földvári. Wings. 45. Chvalaea amazonica Ale-Rocha, 2006, holotype ♀; 46. Chvalaea annularis sp. nov., holotype ♂; 47. Chvalaea boliviana Ale-Rocha, 2006, paratype ♀; 48. Chvalaea catarinensis Ale-Rocha, 2006, paratype ♂; 49. Chvalaea ecuadoriensis sp. nov., paratype ♂; 50. Chvalaea masneri Ale-Rocha, 2006, paratype ♀; 51. Chvalaea pulchra Ale-Rocha, 2006, holotype ♀; 52. Chvalaea sinclairi sp. nov., holotype ♂. Abbreviations: bm = basal medial cell; br = basal radial cell; cua = anterior cubital cell; CuA+CuP = anterior branch of cubital vein + posterior branch of cubital vein; dm = discal medial cell; M 1 = first branch of media; M 4 = fourth branch of media; R 1 = anterior branch of radius; R 2+3 = second branch of radius; R 4+5 = third branch of radius. Scale bars = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2612729/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="349">Fig. 46</figureCitation>
). All coxae whitish yellow, except basal two-thirds of fore coxa brown; hind femur slightly clavate, whitish yellow on basal third, with a wide black ring medially, yellow apically with narrow black apical ring (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 5–8" captionStartId="3.[151,264,987,1009]" captionTargetBox="[188,1398,193,965]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[188,1398,193,965]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 5–8. Chvalaea Papp &amp; Földvári. 5–6. Mediotergite. 5. Chvalaea pulchra Ale-Rocha, 2006, large central black mark highlighted; 6: Chvalaea annularis sp. nov. 7–8. Hind femur. 7. Chvalaea pulchra Ale-Rocha, 2006; 8. Chvalaea annularis sp. nov., black medium ring highlighted. Scale bars: Figs 5–6 = 0.2 mm; Figs 7–8 = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2612709/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="349">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
); all tibiae pale brown except hind tibia black; fore and mid tarsomeres 3–4 and hind tarsomeres 3–5 with short, blunt, black spine-like ventral setae.
</paragraph>
