<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="351" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1654,1935]" pageId="4" pageNumber="351">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1691,1716]" pageId="4" pageNumber="351">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Barros &amp; Soares &amp; Freitas-Silva &amp; Ale-Rocha, 2019" authorityName="Barros &amp; Soares &amp; Freitas-Silva &amp; Ale-Rocha" authorityYear="2019" box="[322,544,1691,1715]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Chvalaea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="351" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="annularis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[322,544,1691,1715]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="351">Chvalaea annularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[552,642,1691,1716]" pageId="4" pageNumber="351">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[552,642,1691,1716]" pageId="4" pageNumber="351" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ale-Rocha" authorityYear="2006" box="[790,910,1691,1715]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Chvalaea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="351" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pulchra">
<emphasis box="[790,910,1691,1715]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="351">C. pulchra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the presence of a broad median stripe, spot on the notopleuron and narrow region above notopleuron, both dark brown, veins M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1092,1100,1742,1756]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="351">1</subScript>
and M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1179,1187,1742,1756]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="351">4</subScript>
not reaching the wing margin, and fore and mid tarsomeres 3–4 and hind tarsomeres 3–5 with short, blunt, black ventral spine-like setae. In 
<taxonomicName authority="Barros &amp; Soares &amp; Freitas-Silva &amp; Ale-Rocha, 2019" authorityName="Barros &amp; Soares &amp; Freitas-Silva &amp; Ale-Rocha" authorityYear="2019" box="[184,327,1802,1826]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Chvalaea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="351" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="annularis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[184,327,1802,1826]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="351">C. annularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[338,431,1801,1826]" pageId="4" pageNumber="351">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[338,431,1801,1826]" pageId="4" pageNumber="351" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, the pronotum, scutellum and mediotergite are dark brown, whereas in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ale-Rocha" authorityYear="2006" box="[1268,1391,1802,1826]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Chvalaea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="351" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pulchra">
<emphasis box="[1268,1391,1802,1826]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="351">C. pulchra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the pronotum and scutellum are yellow and the mediotergite is yellow with a black spot. Moreover, 
<taxonomicName authority="Barros &amp; Soares &amp; Freitas-Silva &amp; Ale-Rocha, 2019" authorityName="Barros &amp; Soares &amp; Freitas-Silva &amp; Ale-Rocha" authorityYear="2019" box="[1252,1394,1838,1862]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Chvalaea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="351" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="annularis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1252,1394,1838,1862]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="351">C. annularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="351">
<taxonomicNameLabel pageId="4" pageNumber="351" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
has the hind femur slightly clavate with a wide black ring medially; in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ale-Rocha" authorityYear="2006" box="[1013,1134,1874,1898]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Chvalaea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="351" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pulchra">
<emphasis box="[1013,1134,1874,1898]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="351">C. pulchra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the hind femur is strongly clavate, yellow with a very narrow, dark brown apical ring.
</paragraph>
